{{!< default}}
{{!--
Template Name: Links / Blogroll
Description: Sites I love - a community-minded collection of recommendations

The blogroll is a beautiful, almost-lost tradition of the early web.
It's about community over competition. Sharing over hoarding.
These are the corners of the internet that inspire me.
--}}

{{#post}}
<article class="links-layout {{post_class}}">

    <div class="links-container">
        {{!-- Header --}}
        <header class="links-header reveal-on-scroll">
            <h1 class="links-title kinetic-text">Links</h1>
            <p class="links-intro">
                Corners of the internet I love.
                People making good things.
                Ideas worth spreading.
            </p>
        </header>

        {{!-- Main content with link cards --}}
        {{!--
            In the Ghost editor, use HTML cards with this structure:

            <div class="links-grid">
                <a href="https://example.com" class="link-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <h3 class="link-card-title">Site Name</h3>
                    <p class="link-card-description">Why I love this site...</p>
                    <span class="link-card-url">example.com</span>
                </a>
            </div>
        --}}

        <div class="links-body gh-content reveal-on-scroll">
            {{content}}
        </div>

        {{!-- Footer --}}
        <footer class="links-footer reveal-on-scroll">
            <p class="links-note">
                This is a <a href="https://blogroll.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">blogroll</a> â€”
                a tradition from the early web where we shared the sites we loved.
                Community over competition.
            </p>
        </footer>
    </div>

</article>
{{/post}}
